2.Change the name of city ‘calicut’ to ‘kozhikode’ in the customer table. 


mysql> select * from CUST;
+---------+--------+------------+------+-------------+
| CUST_ID | NAME   | ADDRESS    | CITY | PH_NO       |
+---------+--------+------------+------+-------------+
|       1 | ASWIN  | KIZHAKKOTH | KKD  | 9743787277  |
|       2 | ARJUN  | PANNUR     | EKM  | 9743787276  |
|       3 | ARUN   | VATOLI     | TVM  | 9743787272  |
|       4 | JITHU  | VATOLI     | WND  |             |
|       5 | JUNAID | KODUVALLY  | MLP  | 9876589986  |
+---------+--------+------------+------+-------------+
5 rows in set (0.00 sec)

mysql> 
mysql> update CUST set CITY='KOZHIKODE' where CUST_ID=1;
Query OK, 1 row affected (0.51 sec)
Rows matched: 1  Changed: 1  Warnings: 0

mysql> select * from CUST;
+---------+--------+------------+-----------+-------------+
| CUST_ID | NAME   | ADDRESS    | CITY      | PH_NO       |
+---------+--------+------------+-----------+-------------+
|       1 | ASWIN  | KIZHAKKOTH | KOZHIKODE | 9743787277  |
