3.Update all prices with 2% of its original price.


mysql> update PRODUCT set PRICE=PRICE*(2/100);
Query OK, 8 rows affected (0.22 sec)
Rows matched: 8  Changed: 8  Warnings: 0

mysql> select * from PRODUCT;
+------+----------------+-------+
| P_ID | P_NAME         | PRICE |
+------+----------------+-------+
|   10 | CRICKET_BAT    |   240 |
|   11 | CRICKET_BALL   |    10 |
|   12 | CRICKET_PAD    |    40 |
|   13 | CRICKET HELMET |    80 |
|   14 | STUMPS         |    20 |
|   15 | GLOWS          |     2 |
|   16 | CAP            |   1.6 |
|   17 | JERSY          |   2.4 |
+------+----------------+-------+
8 rows in set (0.00 sec)

